article.headline: Jackson State 81, Prairie View 68
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 31 points and had nine rebounds to help lead Jackson State to an 81-68 win over Prairie View A&M on Saturday night. Johnson, who was 10-of-19 from the field, had three 3-pointers for the Tigers (12-12, 8-4 Southwestern Athletic). Julius Young came off the bench to add 17 points. Prairie View, which trailed by only three at the half, was outscored 41-31 in the second half. Chris Gaines scored 17 points and Oscar Thompson added 13 and had six rebounds for the Panthers (3-19, 0-11). Clifford Franks came off the bench to score 10 points and grab a team-high 11 rebounds.
